                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "I've been keeping https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/ARROW/Release+Management+Guide#ReleaseManagementGuide-UpdatingRpackages up to date. The only thing not mentioned there is that I generally make a branch on my fork off of the release tag ({{apache-arrow-x.y.z}}) where I add/cherry-pick any extra commits we need for the CRAN release. Sometimes this is just deleting the line in the README with the badges to avoid spurious URL check failures.\r\n\r\nThe other thing not mentioned there, now that I look at it, is doing reverse dependency checks.",
